        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): allow model fallback on harness-owned prompt timeout",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nWhen a harness-owned transport (Ollama, OpenRouter, ...) times out at the prompt stage, `resolveRunFailoverDecision` returns `surface_error` unconditionally, preempting the `fallbackConfigured` guard below. Operators who configured explicit model fallbacks (e.g. Ollama primary with OpenRouter/Claude fallback) see the timeout surface to the user with no fallback attempt.\n\nRoot cause: the early return at the prompt-stage `harnessOwnsTransport && timeout` check does not consult `fallbackConfigured` before surfacing the error.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/failover-policy.ts`: Add the `fallbackConfigured && failoverFailure` guard to the harness-owned prompt timeout early-return. When an explicit fallback model is configured, the timeout now falls through to the fallback_model path.\n- `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/failover-policy.test.ts`: Add two prompt-stage test cases. Update the pre-existing assertion that expected the old buggy surface_error behavior.\n- `scripts/repro/issue-95574-harness-timeout-fallback.mts`: Real behavior proof script.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed**: Harness-owned transport prompt timeout now falls back to the next configured model instead of surfacing \"LLM request timed out.\"\n\n**Real environment tested**: Windows 10, Node.js v22.19.2, source tree at commit e2bb4c8fc1.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n- `node --import tsx scripts/repro/issue-95574-harness-timeout-fallback.mts`\n\n**Evidence after fix**:\n```text\nPASS: harness timeout + fallback -> fallback_model (reason: timeout)\nPASS: harness timeout + no fallback -> surface_error (reason: timeout)\nPASS: non-harness timeout + fallback -> fallback_model\n\nALL CHECKS PASSED — harness-owned prompt timeout honors fallback config.\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix**: Before the fix, all three harness timeout cases returned `surface_error`. After the fix:\n1. harness timeout + fallback configured -> `fallback_model` (the fix)\n2. harness timeout + no fallback -> `surface_error` (preserved)\n3. non-harness timeout + fallback -> `fallback_model` (unchanged)\n\n**What was not tested**: Live Ollama timeout round-trip against a real model. The fix is unit-level, driven by `resolveRunFailoverDecision` which is the single decision function the runtime uses.\n\n## Verification\n\n- 33/33 failover-policy tests pass (vitest).\n- 3/3 real behavior proof checks pass (node-tsx repro script).\n- No other files changed.\n\nFixes #95574\n",
        "branch": "fix/prompt-timeout-harness-fallback",
